      "content": "thanks. that \"raw/tough\" thing makes sense. i guess what i'm really looking for is more specific detail so we don't mess up the imagery. when we talk about \"urban\" or \"street\" vibes, there's usually a lot of overlap with specific communities, right? like, if we're looking at the core inspirations for this look, what specific racial or ethnic influences should we be referencing to make it feel legitimate?",
